<br>
And for vox, i would have sent all the tank in at once, and once vox is at say 60, send in all the nukers...  to burn her down..  and of course the enchanters with the tanks to drain her mana fast....<br>
<br>
You MIGHT be able to hit vox if she is tashia'd and malised...  Not sure though, i hit trak (lvl 65) at lvl 55 for full dmg..  so im not sure about how dragon mobs go about being hit with nukes and so forth...  <br>
<br>
but overall, i think the leader had poor communication in not telling you to be in melee range for nukes...  And not bringing the proper nuking power...  Shrug, just my opinion..<br>
<br>
 <p>Nilerek, level 55 Magician of Quellious<Br>Tilnam, level 32 Rogue of Vazaelle<Br>Kazdun, iksar monk of sullon zek (cant give away my level on pvp) :></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufazzenbinsaladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fazzen Binsaladin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(8/13/01 12:51:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=281.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Vox Raids... </span><hr size=1> A mage's main role on a Vox raid is keeping the pet in the fight, not launching nukes.  Mages can basically bring the strength of 2-3 tanks into the battle (depending on how long it goes).  You have three areas of contribution:<br>
<br>
1.  Keep your pet(s) up and fighting Vox.  <br>
2.  Keep your group Fire shielded.<br>
3.  Keep yourself alive so you can do #1.  <br>
<br>
This means have your pet ready before the go signal (with pet taunt off). Have Vox in target window.  <br>
<br>
When go signal is given for casters, send in your pet to attack.  <br>
<br>
Pay very close attention to when Vox casts her AE spell. <br>
<br>
After an AE cast is complete, run into her lair/cavern, hang a sharp left, and move way out of AE range.  Now stand and watch your pet health.  As pets die, summon new ones and send them in.  If you feel squirrely try shooting an occasional bolt (but don't expect much).<br>
<br>
I can't stress enough the importance of staying out of AE range.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck, <p>Fazzen Binsaladin <br>
